  "narration": "You stagger across the rune-lit floor, sheathing your bloodied sword as you approach Elen. She slumps, trembling and breathless, her hair matted and face streaked with tears and soot. As you kneel beside her and draw her into your arms, she clings to you for support, wracked by relieved sobs.\n\nElen manages a weak, grateful smile, looking up through exhausted, red-rimmed eyes. \"Norn... I thought the darkness would swallow me for good. I tried to buy time, to keep it distracted, but I... I was so tired.\" She lets out a ragged laugh, half-sob, half-disbelief. \"You actually did it. The whispers are gone. I can feel my own heartbeat again.\"\n\nShe squeezes your arm, her grip growing steadier. \"Are you hurt? I saw those things--the shadows. We have to get you out of here. But... thank you. Not just for me, but for everyone lost to this place.\"\n\nThe chamber is quiet, the relic's remains drifting away like mist. A faint, peaceful light plays along the stone pillars, and the oppressive weight of the curse is gone. Above, the keep is silent for the first time in centuries.\n\nElen draws a shaky breath and tries to rise, leaning on your shoulder. \"Tell me what happened, Norn. How did you free us? Did you find... the Knight's heart?\"",
